<white>synopsys:</>
    the command <green>egrep</> is used to filter the output of another
    command in the sense that only lines that are matching a regular expression
    pattern are returned.
    
    the egrep command is intended to be used via a pipe.
    
<white>usage: </><light_gray>$command</> | <green>egrep</> <cyan>$pattern</>

<white>arguments:</>
    <light_gray>$command</> - although command is not an argument of the egrep
               command, it is here for illustrating purposes.
    
    <green>egrep</>     - the <green>egrep</> command
    
    <cyan>$pattern</> - a pattern representing a regular expression.

<white>examples:</>
    ls | <green>egrep</> <cyan>[0-9]+</>
    ls | <green>egrep</> <cyan>Cat[e|g|o|r|y]+</>
